To calculate the LIX readability score, we'll follow the LIX (Läsbarhetsindex) formula, which is a measure of readability developed by the Swedish researcher Carl-Hugo Björnsson. The formula is as follows:

LIX = (antas ord + komplexa ord) × 100 / antal meningar
 där 
antas ord = antal ord / antal meningar
komplexa ord = antal ord med mer än 6 bokstäver i varje mening

